      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Many climate scientists suggest that the transition needs to be extremely rapid to meet global warming targets, implying that renewables alone might not scale fast enough on their own. Advocates for nuclear stress that its baseload capability provides the stable power needed *now* to bridge the gap until renewables are fully robust. Therefore, many experts view nuclear energy as a necessary, though not singular, component of a successful, aggressive climate mitigation strategy.",
